<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Branding &amp; Commercial on RaihnForge</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/</link><description>Recent content in Branding &amp; Commercial on RaihnForge</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 30 Sep 2020 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>SMS Graphics — Mercer Creek Church</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/sms-church-graphics/</link><pubDate>Wed, 30 Sep 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/sms-church-graphics/</guid><description>&lt;p>This project was an opportunity to grow into a graphic style I wasn&amp;rsquo;t already comfortable with. Mercer Creek Church had a clear visual identity and a consistent content cycle — which meant I was learning to adapt to someone else&amp;rsquo;s established system, not just executing my own ideas.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>That&amp;rsquo;s a different skill. When you work within an existing design language, you have to study it carefully: the color palette, the typefaces, the spacing, the emotional register. Then you have to produce work that feels native to it, not like something grafted on from outside.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Honey Badger Decal</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/honey-badger-decal/</link><pubDate>Fri, 12 Oct 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/honey-badger-decal/</guid><description>&lt;p>An original honey badger character design built around the motto &amp;ldquo;NEVER QUIT!&amp;rdquo; — produced as a decal and later adapted into a desktop wallpaper.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Honey Badger Decal Wallpaper</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/honey-badger-decal-wallpaper/</link><pubDate>Fri, 12 Oct 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/honey-badger-decal-wallpaper/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/wp-imports/art/honeybadgerdt_joshuakeyes.png" alt="honeybadgerDT_JoshuaKeyes">&lt;/p>
&lt;p>NEVER QUIT! :D&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This is a design I initially made for my dad, but I enjoyed it enough that I made a wallpaper for myself and have been using it now for many years. I would love to make T-Shirts with the design, but alas I have not yet. I&amp;rsquo;ve also received a great many requests to utilize this in many arenas. I apricate the requests and if you&amp;rsquo;d like to share where you&amp;rsquo;re using it, please post below or email me so I may add your contribution to this post. Thank you!&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Collectable Supplies Coupon</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/collectable-supplies-coupon/</link><pubDate>Thu, 10 Oct 2013 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/collectable-supplies-coupon/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/collectible_supplies_discount_04.jpg">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/collectible_supplies_discount_04.jpg" alt="collectible_supplies_discount_04" title="collectible_supplies_discount_04">&lt;/a>I’ve been privileges enough to do some work for Collectible Supplies from time to time.  This was a very fun and challenging coupon to design, but I feel like in the end the work paid off!  Still, I feel like I could have done a better job with the message text.&lt;/p>
&lt;h6>&lt;/h6>
&lt;h6 id="--oct-2012-design">&lt;em>- Oct 2012 design&lt;/em>&lt;/h6>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/collectible_supplies_discount_138810.png">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/collectible_supplies_discount_138810.png" alt="collectible_supplies_discount_138810" title="collectible_supplies_discount_138810">&lt;/a>  Updated design Oct 2013.  Cleaned up some fonts and removed the holiday theme.
Check out &lt;a href="http://www.collectible-supplies.com/" title="http://www.collectible-supplies.com/">Collectible-Supplies.com&lt;/a>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Team Eve Gaming Logo</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/team-eve-gaming-logo/</link><pubDate>Thu, 31 May 2012 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/team-eve-gaming-logo/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/eve_logo_large.png">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/eve_logo_large.png" alt="eve_logo_large" title="eve_logo_large">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Creating Team Eve’s logo was a rewarding experience, and a test of the process of achieving a shared vision with a client.  Below I discuss the process I used to communicate online, across the globe, to deliver not only a logo for an up and coming eSports team, but some working assets for their web and streaming needs.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>PHASE 1 - INTENT&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;hr>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/wp-imports/gamedev/1.png" alt="1">&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Establish Intent - The above image compiled the sources that I asked the client bring to me as direction on how we might evaluate their personal tastes for their design and their intent.  I want the final product to represent as best as possible the client&amp;rsquo;s unique identity as well as resolve their professional needs.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Honey Badger Logo</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/honey-badger-logo/</link><pubDate>Tue, 10 Apr 2012 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/honey-badger-logo/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/honeybadger_02.png">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/honeybadger_02.png" alt="honeybadger_02" title="honeybadger_02">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I tacked a fun logo project for the ‘PBR STREETGANG’, TEAM HONEY BADGER.  The group requested a Honey Badger as their logo with a military theme.  The client wanted only two colors for printing cost purposes.  Team Honey Badger plans to make a sticker of the logo.  Perhaps even paint one on their Street Bikes for maximum exposure.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I enjoyed creating this rambo like rodent.  The challenge of utilizing limited colors in a Logo that could be shrunk considerably can not be overlooked though.  in the end I believe the final product works well for its purpose.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>USAF Bulldogs T-Shirt</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/usaf-bulldogs-t-shirt/</link><pubDate>Mon, 18 Jul 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/usaf-bulldogs-t-shirt/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/bulldogs_tshirt.jpg">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/bulldogs_tshirt.jpg" alt="bulldogs_tshirt" title="bulldogs_tshirt">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>T-shirt design is for an Air Force BMT Flight, and dedicated to my wife &lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Bulldogs-t-shirt_C494/wlEmoticon-openmouthedsmile.png" alt="Open-mouthed smile">.  Training Instructor and bulldog transformer characters prepare to ROLL OUT (or perhaps flight out?)!  Having very little communication with the client meant that I would have to rely on well thought out assumptions more than anything.  The original request was a transformers version of a Training Instructor with a Pit-bull on a chain leash.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Team Web Building</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/team-web-building/</link><pubDate>Fri, 01 Jul 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/team-web-building/</guid><description>&lt;p>Most of the websites I’ve ever worked on have been with Teams across the Globe.  The client in Europe must have his intent fulfilled.  The Web coder in California must understand some of the subtlety of design.  The artist must uphold the integrity of the design.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Here is a snippet of interaction during a web development cycle.  This is the first iteration of Grubby’s website.  The Photo Gallery was coming along nicely, but needed some extra attention, ensuring the code would reflect the initial design.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Wedding Invitations</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/wedding-invitations/</link><pubDate>Thu, 21 Apr 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/wedding-invitations/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Wedding-Invitations_D253/wedding_invite_blog-post.jpg">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Wedding-Invitations_D253/wedding_invite_blog-post_thumb.jpg" alt="wedding_invite_blog post" title="wedding_invite_blog post">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I created these invites for my best friend’s wedding.  Working with the bride to be we designed some fun invitations to send out.  The original color for them was yellow, but its difficult to get the correct yellow to display on monitors throughout the web, so I changed up the color to blue for this blog post.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Wedding-Invitations_D253/invite_front_blogpost.jpg">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Wedding-Invitations_D253/invite_front_blogpost_thumb.jpg" alt="invite_front_blogpost" title="invite_front_blogpost">&lt;/a>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/invite_back_blogpost.jpg">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/invite_back_blogpost.jpg" alt="invite_back_blogpost" title="invite_back_blogpost">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Wedding-Invitations_D253/rsvp_blogpost.jpg">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Wedding-Invitations_D253/rsvp_blogpost_thumb.jpg" alt="rsvp_blogpost" title="rsvp_blogpost">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>I enjoyed working with my friends on this project.  My favorite part was creating the filigree-like sketches for the floral designs on the corners of the composition.  I hope you enjoyed the invitations! &lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Wedding-Invitations_D253/wlEmoticon-openmouthedsmile.png" alt="Open-mouthed smile">&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Four Oh Four Screen</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/four-oh-four-screen/</link><pubDate>Tue, 19 Apr 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/four-oh-four-screen/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/Untitled-1.jpg">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/Untitled-1.jpg" alt="Untitled-1" title="Untitled-1">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It is customary for websites to have error pages that are somewhat fun. Its frustrating when things break on the internet, so if we are hit with something that makes us smile, it is a bit easier to let go the frustration in running into a glitch.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>For FollowGrubby.com I had the idea of using the ‘King of Blades’ Critical Striking the webpage. This idea came to mind as I was thinking of the numbers involved with the error screens. I am, of course a huge fan of Warcraft 3, so when thinking of something that related to such a huge number as 404, I quickly found myself seeing Critical Strike numbers popping out of my poor Arch Mage as he would desperately seek the solace of a Holy Light, and a StormBolt to slow the blade delivered death that was sure to be his destiny.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>WIld Goose Casio Print Designs</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/wild-goose-casio-print-designs/</link><pubDate>Tue, 22 Mar 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/wild-goose-casio-print-designs/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/casino-aniversery2.png">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/casino-aniversery2_thumb.png" alt="casino aniversery2" title="casino aniversery2">&lt;/a>  &lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/Friday-Poker-copy.png">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/Friday-Poker-copy_thumb.png" alt="Friday Poker copy" title="Friday Poker copy">&lt;/a>   &lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/holdem_tournament-copy2.png">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/a965d3aa5f34_F61C/holdem_tournament-copy2_thumb.png" alt="holdem_tournament copy2" title="holdem_tournament copy2">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>These assets were used for a Casino as a way to update some of the look and feel of their promotions and table print outs.  The project was far and away from what I usually work on.  In the end, though the project was very fun and I was able to learn many more interesting techniques in creating fun designs for print of online assets.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>CD Cover Demos for SHIM</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/cd-cover-demos-for-shim/</link><pubDate>Sat, 18 Apr 2009 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/branding/cd-cover-demos-for-shim/</guid><description>&lt;p>The following are demo covers for the band SHIM.&lt;/p>
